**Testability**: The theory makes clear predictions: episodes meeting both criteria should be consolidated, those not meeting them shouldn't be. One could measure whether consolidated semantic nodes improve generalization on structurally similar tasks, whether provenance pointers enable better explanation, and whether the dual threshold outperforms single-criterion consolidation. These are concrete, falsifiable predictions with identifiable experimental protocols.

