### 5. Mechanistic Plausibility
The mechanism is highly plausible. Cognitive neuroscience supports dual memory systems with complementary roles. In computational terms: high uncertainty indicates unfamiliar situations where detailed episodic traces provide anchoring; low uncertainty indicates familiar contexts where compressed semantic knowledge suffices. This aligns with explore/exploit tradeoffs and active learning principles. The entropy-based trigger is a reasonable proxy for "need more detailed information."

### 6. Empirical Testing
