However, the *specific quantitative claims* (20-40% improvements, logarithmic gains up to 20-30 steps, 2-4x larger gains in <5% vs >20% density) appear to be empirical assertions that would require experimental validation in the specific context of text games with language model agents. I cannot verify these precise numbers from established literature, though the directional claims (that outcome attribution helps, especially in sparse reward settings) are consistent with known RL principles.

